      • ensureCodeBlock

        public static <T extends PsiExpression> T ensureCodeBlock(T expression)
        Ensures that given call is surrounded by PsiCodeBlock (that is, it has a parent statement which is located inside the code block). If not, tries to create a code block.

        Note that the expression is not necessarily a child of PsiExpressionStatement; it could be a subexpression, PsiIfStatement, etc.

        This method works if ControlFlowUtils.canExtractStatement(PsiExpression) returns true on the same expression.

        Parameters:
        expression - an expression which should be located inside the code block
        Returns:
        a passed expression if it's already surrounded by code block and no changes are necessary; a replacement expression (which is equivalent to the passed expression) if a new code block was created; null if the expression cannot be surrounded with code block.

      • checkEnumConstantInSwitchLabel

      • transitiveClosure

        public static <T> java.util.Set<T> transitiveClosure(RefactoringUtil.Graph<T> graph,
                                                     Condition<? super T> initialRelation)
        Returns subset of graph.getVertices() that is a transitive closure (by graph.getTargets()) of the following property: initialRelation.value() of vertex or graph.getTargets(vertex) is true.

        Note that graph.getTargets() is not neccesrily a subset of graph.getVertex()

        Parameters:
        graph -
        initialRelation -
        Returns:
        subset of graph.getVertices()
